body:
I don't have a strong feeling either way about it, but I use it in larger functions to distinguish broad-scoping 'function initialization' stuff (config parsing and whatnot) from just jumping into the body of the function. So, 

``` javascript
function (options) {
  var options = options || {};

  // start the body of the function
}
```

Versus

``` javascript
function (options) {

  // first self-contained bit of logic

  // second self-contained bit of logic

  // and so on
}
```

But it's mostly aesthetics plus an old habit, and it does violate our styleguide.

